article.headline: ETSU 92, North Florida 68
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Kenyona Swader scored 19 points and grabbed seven rebounds to lead ETSU to a 92-68 win over North Florida on Sunday. The Bucs (11-9, 5-2 Atlantic Sun Conference) also got 14 points and 11 rebounds from Kevin Tiggs. Travis Strong added 18 points, while Andrew Reed and Courtney Pigram pitched in 12 points apiece. The Bucs out-rebounded the Ospreys 46-35, while forcing North Florida (1-18, 0-7) into 18 turnovers on eight steals. In addition, ETSU hit on 80 percent of its foul shots (28-of-35) and shot 43 percent from the field. ETSU dominated the court in both halfs, leading 48-32 in the first, and 44-36 in the second. North Florida got a team high 17 points from Stan Januska, while Tom Hammonds and Kyle Groothuis netted 14 and 13 points, respectively.
